1
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:48,560
Brother.

2
00:00:49,200 --> 00:00:50,080
Are you awake?

3
00:00:51,080 --> 00:00:53,600
If you don't drink, you can't leave the table.

4
00:00:53,600 --> 00:00:54,400
Brother.

5
00:00:58,360 --> 00:00:59,800
It's been two days, Brother.

6
00:00:59,800 --> 00:01:02,040
Even the chickens behind my house have woken up twice,

7
00:01:02,040 --> 00:01:03,680
and you're just opening your eyes now.

8
00:01:03,680 --> 00:01:06,610
Anan almost went to find a shaman to summon your soul.

9
00:01:08,800 --> 00:01:09,400
Here.

10
00:01:17,520 --> 00:01:18,320
Two days?

11
00:01:20,800 --> 00:01:22,360
I thought I was home.

12
00:01:22,480 --> 00:01:23,080
Brother.

13
00:01:23,600 --> 00:01:25,520
You went around asking people to drink.

14
00:01:25,520 --> 00:01:27,580
You made everyone finish their cups.

15
00:01:27,880 --> 00:01:30,539
When you got drunk, we couldn't even pull you up.

16
00:01:33,280 --> 00:01:33,479
The new drum is easy to use.

17
00:01:33,479 --> 00:01:34,560
The new drum is easy to use.

18
00:01:34,560 --> 00:01:35,400
What new drum?

19
00:01:35,680 --> 00:01:36,539
Brother Liu Ma.

20
00:01:37,440 --> 00:01:38,640
You're so kind.

21
00:01:39,160 --> 00:01:42,420
This one is much more expensive than the one you stepped on.

22
00:01:44,720 --> 00:01:45,800
And my new guitar.

23
00:01:46,479 --> 00:01:47,120
Liuma,

24
00:01:47,520 --> 00:01:48,380
listen to this.

25
00:01:49,680 --> 00:01:50,240
How is it?

26
00:01:50,520 --> 00:01:51,400
What do you think?

27
00:01:51,400 --> 00:01:52,240
Looks good, right?

28
00:01:52,240 --> 00:01:53,100
It looks great.

29
00:01:58,000 --> 00:01:58,600
Liuma,

30
00:01:58,720 --> 00:02:00,640
I'm going to try out the new guitar.

31
00:02:00,640 --> 00:02:01,280
Bye.

32
00:02:02,720 --> 00:02:04,180
I'm telling you right now.

33
00:02:04,440 --> 00:02:05,680
I, Liuma,

34
00:02:06,360 --> 00:02:08,289
will give you the best instruments

35
00:02:08,360 --> 00:02:10,199
in the whole world.

36
00:02:12,440 --> 00:02:15,100
I feel like this guitar is a perfect match for me.

37
00:02:18,600 --> 00:02:19,640
Transfer the money, now.

38
00:02:19,640 --> 00:02:21,079
My patience is limited, bro.

39
00:02:21,079 --> 00:02:23,079
I thought you were just brushing me off.

40
00:02:23,079 --> 00:02:23,680
Turns out, deep down,

41
00:02:23,680 --> 00:02:25,210
you actually care about us.

42
00:02:25,240 --> 00:02:27,240
Honestly, I judged you wrong before.

43
00:02:27,240 --> 00:02:28,920
Anan got it right this time.

44
00:02:34,760 --> 00:02:35,440
Liuma,

45
00:02:36,240 --> 00:02:37,120
actually...

46
00:02:37,680 --> 00:02:39,240
it was nice just to see them.

47
00:02:39,560 --> 00:02:41,560
Let's find a way to sell the instruments.

48
00:02:41,560 --> 00:02:42,280
For your situation.

49
00:02:42,280 --> 00:02:43,040
Anan,

50
00:02:47,320 --> 00:02:48,960
that competition you mentioned.

51
00:02:48,960 --> 00:02:49,720
When is it?

52
00:02:52,920 --> 00:02:54,520
There's prize money, right?

53
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:55,520
Right.

54
00:02:55,720 --> 00:02:56,640
It's 100,000.

55
00:02:57,400 --> 00:02:58,600
100,000?

56
00:02:59,960 --> 00:03:01,360
You promise to start a band with us

57
00:03:01,360 --> 00:03:01,760
and join the competition?

58
00:03:01,760 --> 00:03:03,020
Join the competition?

59
00:03:04,400 --> 00:03:05,260
Let me be clear.

60
00:03:05,760 --> 00:03:06,800
I'm not going on stage.

61
00:03:06,800 --> 00:03:08,160
I'll just act as the band manager

62
00:03:08,160 --> 00:03:08,760
to assist you.

63
00:03:08,760 --> 00:03:10,080
Anan, you're still on lead guitar.

64
00:03:10,080 --> 00:03:11,520
If you don't play well, don't expect to sleep.

65
00:03:11,520 --> 00:03:12,040
Liuma,

66
00:03:12,480 --> 00:03:13,640
we'll work together

67
00:03:13,840 --> 00:03:15,700
and help you earn that money back.

68
00:03:16,040 --> 00:03:18,500
If you don't let go, I'm going to regret this.

69
00:03:19,960 --> 00:03:21,640
Then we're still missing a bass.

70
00:03:21,640 --> 00:03:22,280
Right.

71
00:03:23,840 --> 00:03:24,680
Bass.

72
00:03:25,920 --> 00:03:27,079
We'll find a bass player now.

73
00:03:27,079 --> 00:03:27,680
Let's go.

74
00:03:41,840 --> 00:03:42,560
I'm sorry.

75
00:03:42,640 --> 00:03:43,400
Look, I'm so busy.

76
00:03:43,400 --> 00:03:44,520
I have two kids.

77
00:03:59,280 --> 00:04:00,120
Hello, you're here.

78
00:04:00,120 --> 00:04:01,440
Please, come in.

79
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:03,120
Here, have a seat.

80
00:04:03,440 --> 00:04:04,360
A bass master.

81
00:04:04,400 --> 00:04:05,200
A true master.

82
00:04:06,600 --> 00:04:08,060
Let me play a piece for you.

83
00:04:22,360 --> 00:04:23,200
Why are you leaving?

84
00:04:23,200 --> 00:04:23,600
We have things to do.

85
00:04:23,600 --> 00:04:25,130
I can play a different tune.

86
00:04:29,960 --> 00:04:31,040
That dog.

87
00:04:35,240 --> 00:04:37,240
Do you even know how to play the bass?

88
00:04:51,280 --> 00:04:52,610
Let's be clear upfront.

89
00:04:52,720 --> 00:04:53,640
300 a day.

90
00:04:54,159 --> 00:04:55,560
Paid daily. No haggling.

91
00:04:56,120 --> 00:04:56,920
Deal.

92
00:04:57,200 --> 00:04:58,159
Let's run through it.

93
00:04:58,159 --> 00:04:59,159
Build some chemistry.

94
00:04:59,159 --> 00:05:00,840
Come on. Hand out the scores.

95
00:05:02,400 --> 00:05:03,080
No need.

96
00:05:04,520 --> 00:05:05,360
We're all pros here.

97
00:05:05,360 --> 00:05:06,690
I won't go into details.

98
00:05:07,320 --> 00:05:08,380
Let's do Section A.

99
00:05:08,560 --> 00:05:09,280
Drums start.

100
00:05:09,280 --> 00:05:09,840
Okay.

101
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:11,600
Come on.

102
00:05:15,240 --> 00:05:16,000
Jiang.

103
00:05:20,800 --> 00:05:21,440
Okay.

104
00:05:24,360 --> 00:05:26,490
A friend asked me to join another band.

105
00:05:27,040 --> 00:05:28,040
The pay is higher.

106
00:05:28,760 --> 00:05:29,760
Sorry about that.

107
00:05:41,440 --> 00:05:42,640
Here it comes.

108
00:05:45,680 --> 00:05:46,560
Your favorite.

109
00:05:46,640 --> 00:05:47,960
Doesn't your family run a restaurant?

110
00:05:47,960 --> 00:05:49,480
Why didn't we go to your place?

111
00:05:49,480 --> 00:05:51,120
You know how it is at my house.

112
00:05:51,880 --> 00:05:53,010
It's spacious here.

113
00:05:53,159 --> 00:05:54,080
Okay.

114
00:05:56,040 --> 00:05:58,120
Jiang poached our bass player with a high offer.

115
00:05:58,120 --> 00:05:59,120
What do you think?

116
00:06:00,480 --> 00:06:01,880
He's definitely entering the competition.

117
00:06:01,880 --> 00:06:02,680
What a coincidence.

118
00:06:02,680 --> 00:06:04,680
Forming a band at the same time as us.

119
00:06:04,800 --> 00:06:06,530
It's definitely intentional.

120
00:06:07,560 --> 00:06:08,200
How about

121
00:06:09,080 --> 00:06:10,610
we spend a little more money

122
00:06:10,960 --> 00:06:12,480
to find another bass player?

123
00:06:12,480 --> 00:06:13,360
No.

124
00:06:13,840 --> 00:06:14,800
He's inflating prices.

125
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:16,360
It's disrupting the market.

126
00:06:16,360 --> 00:06:17,000
Besides,

127
00:06:17,200 --> 00:06:18,130
that bass player

128
00:06:18,200 --> 00:06:19,930
isn't in it for the music at all.

129
00:06:20,320 --> 00:06:21,280
Hi, guys.

130
00:06:35,240 --> 00:06:36,120
What's wrong?

131
00:06:36,800 --> 00:06:38,560
Weren't we supposed to have dinner?

132
00:06:38,560 --> 00:06:40,020
Why do you all look so down?

133
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:41,930
The bass player bailed.

134
00:06:44,440 --> 00:06:45,720
Just find a new one.

135
00:06:46,680 --> 00:06:47,720
But

136
00:06:48,120 --> 00:06:50,320
what kind of person are you looking for?

137
00:06:50,480 --> 00:06:53,480
Good musical sense, has time, knows instruments.

138
00:06:53,640 --> 00:06:55,000
And preferably,

139
00:06:56,720 --> 00:06:57,920
handsome.

140
00:07:08,800 --> 00:07:10,200
Why are you looking at me?

141
00:07:13,320 --> 00:07:14,180
You're the one.

142
00:07:14,360 --> 00:07:14,920
Me?

143
00:07:30,600 --> 00:07:32,120
Do you really trust me?

144
00:07:32,640 --> 00:07:34,000
We keep the good stuff in the family.

145
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:35,240
Since there's a bonus involved,

146
00:07:35,240 --> 00:07:36,640
how could I leave you out?

147
00:07:36,920 --> 00:07:38,480
The bass is actually quite simple.

148
00:07:38,480 --> 00:07:39,680
It's a lot like the sanxian.

149
00:07:39,680 --> 00:07:40,540
I'll teach you.

150
00:07:40,640 --> 00:07:42,000
Don't worry about your left hand.

151
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:42,860
Just the right.

152
00:07:44,560 --> 00:07:45,040
Good.

153
00:07:45,240 --> 00:07:46,240
Then the sanxian.

154
00:07:46,320 --> 00:07:47,840
For the 3rd string, use two fingers

155
00:07:47,840 --> 00:07:48,920
and rest them on the 4th string.

156
00:07:48,920 --> 00:07:50,080
Keep your thumb anchored here.

157
00:07:50,080 --> 00:07:50,920
Do it eight times.

158
00:07:50,920 --> 00:07:53,040
1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8.

159
00:07:53,040 --> 00:07:53,960
Try again.

160
00:07:54,600 --> 00:07:57,520
1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8.

161
00:07:57,760 --> 00:07:59,560
Not bad. You're talented.

162
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:01,000
You've got a gift.

163
00:08:01,880 --> 00:08:02,400
You...

164
00:08:02,400 --> 00:08:03,600
improvise with your left hand.

165
00:08:03,600 --> 00:08:05,400
Is it a chord like the 3rd string?

166
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:07,640
Pluck the 3rd and 4th strings with your right hand.

167
00:08:07,640 --> 00:08:08,570
Try it yourself.

168
00:08:08,880 --> 00:08:09,560
Let me hear it.

169
00:08:09,560 --> 00:08:13,200
1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8.

170
00:08:15,880 --> 00:08:16,640
I got it.

171
00:08:22,480 --> 00:08:23,240
How was it?

172
00:08:25,840 --> 00:08:26,680
Pretty good.

173
00:08:27,600 --> 00:08:28,200
Really?

174
00:08:29,240 --> 00:08:29,880
Good.

175
00:08:30,280 --> 00:08:30,960
Really.

176
00:08:34,039 --> 00:08:36,240
I feel like I'm joining the music scene.

177
00:08:36,280 --> 00:08:37,640
I need to think about

178
00:08:37,720 --> 00:08:39,200
my fan club name.
